xs<-c(2,0,4,1,3,6,9)
xsbar<-mean(xs)
sample<-srs(xs, n = 4)
XN<-apply(sample, 1, mean) #mean of each sample
sdxn<-apply(sample, 1, var) #variance of each sample
p1n<-fractions(xtabs(~XN)/35)
p2n<-fractions(xtabs(~sdxn)/35)
xbar1<-as.numeric(names(p1n))
sd2<-as.numeric(names(p2n))
MUp1<-sum(xbar1*p1n) #mean of xbar
varp1<-sum((xbar1-MUp1)^2*p1n) #sample variance
musdp2<-sum(sd2*p2n) #population variance or expected value of the sample variance
cbind(MUp1, varp1)
##          MUp1    varp1
## [1,] 3.571429 1.030612
withR<-expand.grid(xs, xs, xs, xs)
xbarN<-apply(withR, 1, mean)
s2N<-apply(withR, 1, var) 
T1<-fractions(xtabs(~xbarN)/9604) 
T2<-fractions(xtabs(~s2N)/9604) #probabilities of each variance
XBAR<-as.numeric(names(T1)) #gets the unique values of xbar
S2<-as.numeric(names(T2)) #gets the unique values of variances
MU_xbarN<-sum(XBAR*T1)
MU_xbarN #here's the mean
## [1] 25/28
VAR_xbarN<-sum((XBAR - MU_xbarN)^2*T1) #sample variance
MU_s2N<-sum(S2*T2)
cbind(MU_xbarN, VAR_xbarN)
##       MU_xbarN VAR_xbarN
## [1,] 0.8928571  2.308992
